<head2>(Choosing Menu Items\paint_choosing)
<p>
Paint offers a wide variety of drawing options.
The menus contain menu items that let you create special effects in your 
picture.
<p>
For example, the Invert menu item on the Edit menu creates a negative image of
the selected portion of a picture.  The Paint program can reverse the 
tones of the selected portion of the picture, switching the foreground 
color and the background color. 
<p>
For information about using the menus, double click on an item from the 
list of additional topics below.



<P>
Additional topics:
<LIST>(UNNUMBERED)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(cshelp)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(overview)
<ENDLIST>
 
<head2>(Erasing\paint_erasing)            
<p>
There are several ways to erase in Paint:


<list>(unnumbered\-)

<le>To erase selected portions of your drawing, use the Eraser.

<le>To erase an entire area, select the
area using the Box tool or the Scissors.  Then choose Cut
from the Edit menu.
<le>To erase the entire visible portion of the canvas, choose Clear Window
from the Edit menu.
<le>To erase all moves made under
your current tool selection, choose Undo from the Edit menu.  In the
Edit menu, Undo is followed by the name of the tool you have selected.  For
example, the Undo Line menu item appears when you select the Line tool.

<endlist>
 


<P>
