<head2>(Using the Grid Option\grid)
<p>
If you want to line up a series of shapes or draw shapes
equidistant to each other, choose Grid On from the Options menu.
<p>
The Grid On option superimposes a horizontal and vertical pattern of dots on 
the drawing window and serves as a guide that does not become part of the
picture.
<p>
The Grid On option is helpful when you are drawing geometric figures.  The 
grid causes lines to "snap into place" on the dots. 

<P>
