<head2>(Drawing Lines and Shapes\paint_drawing_sec)
<p>                                     
The bottom half of the tool palette contains a collection of line and shape
tools that you use in a similar way.   Whenever you draw a straight line or a
shape,  the point where you press MB1 becomes the tool's reference point.  
<p>
You can stretch and swing the line or shape from the 
reference point by dragging the pointer. When
the shape is correct, anchor it in place by releasing MB1.
<p>
For example, to draw a rectangle:

<list>(numbered)
<le>Click on the rectangle tool. 

<le>Point to where you want one corner of the
rectangle to be. Press MB1 and drag diagonally across the drawing
surface until the rectangle has the width and height you want.

<le>To anchor the shape, release MB1.
<endlist>

<P>
