<head2>(Using the Paintbrush\paint_paintbrush)
<p>
The Paintbrush tool applies paint along the path of the pointer. The
Paintbrush is the default tool.
<p> 
Initially, the Paintbrush has a solid stroke, but you can choose a patterned
stroke by changing the outline pattern on the Patterns palette.

<p>
To shape the tip of the Paintbrush: 

<list>(numbered)
<le>Choose Brushes... from the Options menu.  The Brushes dialog box 
appears.

<le>Click on the brush shape you want.
<le>Click on OK.
<le>Move the pointer into the drawing window and try out the new brush 
stroke.
<endlist>


<P>
