<head2>(Selecting Images\paint_editing) 
<p>
Paint's Edit menu items let you easily rearrange images you select
in the
drawing window.   
<p>You can delete selected images entirely, move them to another part of
the window, or copy them.  
<p>
Paint allows you to size selected images,
reducing them or enlarging them as you wish.  Paint can also crop a 
picture,
retaining one section of the canvas while discarding the rest.  
<p>
To select an image, use one of Paint's selection tools:  the 
Box or the Scissors.
<p>
To use the Box, click on the Box
and then position the pointer in one corner of the area you want to select. 
Press MB1 and drag over the desired image. Release MB1.
<p>
To use the Scissors, click on the Scissors and 
then position the pointer near the object you want to select.
Press MB1 and drag the pointer 
around the boundary of the desired object until you reach the starting point.
Release MB1. 
<p>
To select the entire visible portion of the canvas, choose 
Select All from the Edit menu.

<P>
