<head2>(Resizing Images\resiz_image)
<p>
You can modify the proportions of selected images.  
<p>
To scale an image:
<list>(numbered)
<le>Use the Box or the Scissors to select the image you want to modify.
<le>Choose Scale... from the Edit menu.
<p>
Paint displays the Scale dialog box.


<le>For both the x scale and the y scale, click on one of the
percent buttons to change the scale.  

For example, clicking on 25% reduces the selected area to one-fourth the
original size, while clicking on 200% makes it twice as large as the 
original.
<p>To specify your own
percentages, enter a number less than 100 to shrink the figure or a number
greater than 100 to expand the figure.
<endlist>
<p>
To scale your entire picture, choose Scale Window from the Edit menu.
You cannot undo this operation.

<p>
Often, you want to keep only a portion of the picture, and you want to
discard the rest of the canvas.  Use the Crop menu item to extract a
portion of a picture.  

<p>
To crop a picture:
<list>(numbered)
<le>Use the Box or the Scissors to select the section of the picture you 
want to keep.
<le>Choose Crop from the Edit menu.
<p>
Paint repositions the cropped picture in the upper left corner of the 
window
and discards the rest of the picture.
<p>To restore the original picture,
choose Undo Crop from the Edit menu.
<endlist>

<P>
