<head2>(Inserting Text\paint_inserting)
<p> 
You can insert text anywhere in the Paint window. Various fonts are available.

<p>
You
can change the appearance of text in the drawing window until the moment you
click to complete the text entry.  After that, Paint incorporates the text into
the graphic image.  
<p>
To insert text:

<list>(numbered)
<le>Select the Text tool.

<le>Position the pointer in the Paint window where you want to insert
text and click MB1.  

<le>Type in text from the keyboard.

<le> To complete the entry with its current characteristics, either move the
pointer to another part of the window and click MB1 or select another tool. 
<endlist>
<p>
To make changes to the text's font type, pica size, or
format,
choose the appropriate menu item from the Text menu.

<P>
