<head3>(Paste\edit_paste)
<p>
The Paste menu item allows you to put a copy of the contents of the clipboard
onto the canvas.  Paint
can paste graphic images, but it cannot paste text.
<p>
To paste a copy of an image on your canvas, choose Paste from the Edit 
menu.
<p>
Paint puts a copy of the image on the canvas, leaving it selected.  A copy 
of the image remains in the clipboard for later use.
<p>
To move the image, position the pointer inside the selected area and drag 
the image to the location of your choice.
<p>
To cancel the selection, click in another part of the window or select 
another tool.

<P>
