<head3>(Picture Size...\options_picture_size)
<p>
The Picture Size... menu item allows you to change the dimensions of the current 
canvas.
<p>
To change the dimensions of the canvas:
<list>(numbered)
<le>Choose Picture Size... from the Options menu.  The Picture Size 
dialog box appears.
<p>
The Picture Size dialog box shows the current canvas size with its 
dimensions
converted to pixels, inches, or centimeters.
<le>To specify how you are changing the Paint window, click on either the 
Crop or Scale radio button.
<le>In the Size check button, press MB1 on the push button; an Options menu
appears.  Drag to the size you want:  Letter, Screen, or Non-Standard.
Release MB1.  
<p>
If you chose Letter or Screen, the size appears in the Size 
check button.
<p>
If you chose Non-Standard, click on the Width and Height check buttons
and enter the 
measurements you want.
<le>To set the dimensions to be in pixels, inches, or
centimeters, click on the appropriate radio button.  The measurements in the 
Width and Height check buttons change accordingly.
<p>
If you chose
Non-Standard from the Size options menu, 
type in the height and width you want.
The maximum 
size
is 2550 by 3300 pixels, and the minimum size is 10 by 10 pixels.
    
<le>To set the resolution, press MB1 on the push button in the Resolution 
check button.  Drag to the resolution you want: 75, 100, or 300 dpi (dots per 
inch), or Non-Standard.  Release MB1.
<p>
If you chose 75, 100, or 300 dpi, the resolution appears in the Resolution 
check button.
<p>
If you chose Non-Standard, click on the Dots per inch check button and 
enter the resolution you want.  
<le>Click on OK.  The canvas size changes to your specification.
<endlist>


<P>
