<head3>(Opaque and Transparent\options_opaque_trans)
<p>
The Opaque and Transparent menu items allow you to choose how the images 
appear.
<p>
Most of the time, geometric shapes or figures are opaque; you
cannot see what lies behind them.  
<p>Opaque figures are the default, as 
indicated
by the shaded option button next to the Opaque menu item on the Options 
menu.
<p>If you choose Transparent from the Options menu, the background images show
through  the foreground images.  
<p>The Transparent and Opaque settings affect
not only figures but selected images being moved, and the Spray Can, 
Paintbrush, and Text tools.
    


<P>
