<head3>(Paint View and Full View\options_paint_view)
<p>
The Paint View and Full View menu items allow you to specify which portion 
of the canvas you want to display.

<p>Paint View is the default, as 
indicated
by the shaded option button next to the Paint View menu item on the Options 
menu.
With Paint View, only the Paint window is displayed.
<p>
If you choose Full View, you see the entire canvas.
In Full View mode, the only tool available is
the Rectangle.
<p>
To crop the picture in Full View mode, choose Crop from the Edit menu.
<p>
To return to the Paint window, choose Paint View from the Options menu.
The canvas is rescaled and the Paint window appears.
   

<P>
