<head3>(Zoom On/Off\options_zoom)
<p>
The Zoom On and Zoom Off menu items allow you to magnify portions of the
canvas and then return to the standard sizing.
<p>
Zoom acts like a magnifying glass in the drawing window, enlarging
an image to eight times its original size.  

<p>                         
To magnify a portion of the canvas:

<list>(numbered)
<le>Choose Zoom On from the Options menu. 
<p>             
The Zoom window opens beside the Paint window and you see
a magnifying frame 
in the Paint window itself.  The magnifying frame in the Paint window
demonstrates the size of the image that Paint magnifies in the Zoom window. 
<p>
To edit a larger area of the canvas, you can resize the Zoom window,

<le>Place the pointer inside the magnifying frame and drag the frame over the
image that you want to edit. 

<p>
Notice that the Zoom window contains an enlarged version of the image that is
defined by the magnifying frame in the Paint window.

<le>Select the Pencil tool from the tool palette.

<le>Bring the pointer into the Zoom window and use the Pencil to add  fine
details to the image. Either click on individual pixels or draw over them. 
<endlist>

<p>
To close the Zoom window, choose Zoom Off from the Options menu.




<P>
