<head2>(Selection Box\box)
<p>
Use the Box tool to select a rectangular area for editing.


<head2>(Selection Scissors\scissors)
<p>
Use the Scissors tool to select a shape for editing.


<head2>(Spray Can\spray_can)
<p>
Use the Spray Can tool to apply paint in the current outline pattern.  (The
slower the drag,  the darker the coat.)
                                                         
<p>
By default, the Spray Can fill pattern is solid and is determined
by the foreground color.

<head2>(Pencil\pencil)
<p>
Use the Pencil tool to draw a thin line. You can shift-click the Pencil to 
create a 90-degree stroke.
                
<head2>(Eraser\eraser)
<p>
Use the Eraser tool to delete the image in the path of the pointer. You can 
shift-click the Eraser to 
create a 90-degree stroke.
                

<head2>(Paintbrush\paint_brush)
<p>
The Paintbrush is the default
paint tool.
<p>
Use the Paintbrush to paint a free stroke. You can shift-click the 
Paintbrush to 
create a 90-degree stroke. 
                
<p>
By default, the Paintbrush fill pattern is solid and is determined by
the foreground color.

<head2>(Text Tool\text_tool)
<p>
Use the Text tool to add text to the picture.                           


<head2>(Paint Bucket\paint_bucket)
<p>
Use the Paint Bucket tool to fill a closed shape with the current fill pattern.
<p>
Note that you can fill a pattern only within the confines
of the Paint window.

<head2>(Line\line)
<p>
Use the Line tool to draw a straight line. You can shift-click for 
a 45-degree or a 90-degree angle.


<head2>(Arc\arc)
<p>
Use the Arc tool to sketch a horizontal or vertical arc, depending on the 
initial
movement after the click. You can shift-click to draw a quarter circle.


<head2>(Rectangle\rectangle)
<p>
Use the Rectangle tool to draw a rectangle. You can shift-click to 
draw a square.


<head2>(Square\square)
<p>
Use the Square tool to draw a square.


<head2>(Ellipse\ellipse)
<p>
Use the Ellipse tool to draw an oval shape. You can shift-click 
to draw a circle.


<head2>(Circle\circle)
<p>
Use the Circle tool to draw a circle.



<head2>(Free-Hand Stroke\free_stroke)
<p>
Use the Free-Hand Stroke tool to draw 
a free-hand line in the current line width
and pattern.


<head2>(Polyline\polyline)
<p>
Use the Polyline tool to 
draw a multisided figure.  You click to specify a corner, and you
double click to complete a shape.  When you complete 
a shape, the polyline ends and you can begin another.
<p>
You can shift-click for 45-degree or 90-degree
angles.
<p>
Note that clicking near the starting point of the polyline closes
the polygon and completes the shape.

<head2>(Dropper\dropper)
<p>
Use the Dropper tool to pick up the current pixel color (for 
color monitors only).

<head2>(Canvas Area\whole_canvas_box)
<p>
The area of the canvas, with the display window enclosed, appears at the 
bottom of the tool palette as a box within a box.

<p>
Use these boxes to display different areas of the canvas quickly.
Click anywhere 
in the boxed area; the canvas display moves accordingly.
<p>
Alternatively, you can use the horizontal and vertical scroll bars to 
navigate the canvas.

