<head2>(Using Scroll Bars\using_scrolls)
<p>
You can use the vertical and horizontal scroll bars to display information outside 
the borders of the Paint window. 
<p>A scroll bar has stepper
arrows at each end of a
scroll region and a slider within the scroll region. 

<p>
For more information about using scroll bars and arrows, double click 
on one of the additional topics below.

<P>
Additional topics:
<LIST>(UNNUMBERED)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(stepping_arrows)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(scroll_region)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(slider)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(cshelp)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(overview)
<ENDLIST>
 
<head3>(Using Stepper Arrows\stepping_arrows)
<p>
 Stepper arrows are the triangles that appear at 
 each end of the vertical or horizontal scroll bars.
<p>
 To move the window one line in the direction of the
 stepper arrow, move the pointer to a stepper arrow and click MB1. 
 This action allows you to scroll through the information in the window at a 
slow pace.
<p>
To move the window continuously in the direction of the stepper
arrow, move the pointer to a stepper arrow.
Press and hold MB1. This action allows you to scroll through the
information in the window at a faster pace.

<P>
Additional topics:
<LIST>(UNNUMBERED)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(cshelp)
<ENDLIST>
 
<head3>(Using the Scroll Region\scroll_region)

<p>
 The scroll region is the area between the stepper
 arrows that does not fit in the window.
<p>
To move the information in the window by one
window length, move the pointer to the scroll region and click MB1.

<P>
Additional topics:
<LIST>(UNNUMBERED)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(cshelp)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(overview)
<ENDLIST>
 
<head3>(Using the Slider\slider)
<p>
 The slider is the rectangle in
 the scroll bar. The slider shows you how
 much information is still hidden.  For example, if
 the slider takes up 10 percent of the scrolling region, only
 10 percent of the information appears in the window.  The other 90 percent 
remains hidden.
<p>
 To move quickly through the information, move the pointer to the
 slider. Press MB1, and drag the slider up and down through the
 scrolling region. When you release MB1, the information
 from the position in the information indicated by the slider is
 displayed in the window.

