<head2>(Using the Save As Dialog Box\save_as_dbox)
<p>
When you choose Save As... from the File menu, the Save As dialog box 
appears.
<p>
In the Selection entry box, type the file name for the picture.  
<p>
The default file 
 format for the CDA Viewer is Digital Document Interchange
 Format (DDIF). 
<p>
 DDIF is a
 standard format for the storage and interchange of
 compound documents. Compound documents contain multiple
 elements, for example, text and graphics.
<p>To choose X11 file format, click on the X11 radio button.
<p>
The default output is black and white.  To choose Gray or Color, click on 
the appropriate radio button.
<p>
Click on OK to save the file under the file name you specified, or click on 
Cancel to return to the picture without saving it.

