<head2>(Using the Grid Dialog Box\grid_dbox)
<p>
When you choose Grid Size... from the Options menu, the Grid dialog box 
appears.

<p>
The Grid dialog box allows you to change the size of the grid, which is a 
horizontal and vertical pattern of dots that is superimposed on the drawing 
window.  If you select Grid On from the Options menu, the grid appears.
<p>
To change the size of the grid:
<list>(numbered)
<le>
Press MB1 on the slider and drag to the size you want.  Release 
MB1.
<p>
The higher 
the number, the farther apart the dots will be.
The default grid size is 19 pixels; the range is from 8 to 100 pixels.
<le>Click on OK.
<endlist>

<P>
